## What Changes Per Problem — The Only Variable Part

The template is always the same. The only thing that changes is **what you track** inside the window:

| Problem Type | What You Track | Add/Remove Logic |
|---|---|---|
| Max/Min sum | integer sum | `sum + incoming - outgoing` |
| Average | integer sum → divide | same as above |
| Max distinct chars | HashMap of frequencies | increment incoming key, decrement outgoing key, remove if zero |
| Fixed window anagram | frequency array of size 26 | increment incoming char index, decrement outgoing char index |
| Count of ones / condition | integer count | `count + incoming - outgoing` (if they are 1s) |

---

## The One Rule to Never Forget

> **The outgoing element is always at index `i - k`, not `i - k + 1` or `i - 1`.**

This trips people up. At the moment you process index `i` as incoming, the element that just fell outside the window is exactly `k` steps behind it.

---

## Your Practice Checklist for This Pattern

Work these in order — same template, increasing complexity of what you track:

1. Maximum sum of k elements ← start here, pure sum
2. Average of all subarrays of size k ← same as above, just divide
3. First negative number in every window of size k ← track a deque of negatives
4. Count occurrences of anagram in a string ← track a frequency array

Once you can do all four from memory, fixed window is locked in.